00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:49,940
 "and are trying to pervert the gospel of Christ."

283
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:52,620
 So Paul, he is astonished.

284
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:55,020
 He is exasperated.

285
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:56,740
 He is dumbfounded.

286
00:13:56,740 --> 00:14:00,300
 Like, what's wrong with you people?

287
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:02,180
 That's what he's saying.

288
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:03,220
 Like, what happened?

289
00:14:03,220 --> 00:14:06,620
 I was just there with you not that long ago.

290
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:09,580
 And now suddenly you're on this totally different track.

291
00:14:09,580 --> 00:14:11,220
 I mean, he really can't help himself,

292
00:14:11,220 --> 00:14:13,680
 but expresses his surprise.

293
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:18,420
 And they were deserting the,

294
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:20,660
 they were not living anymore,

295
00:14:20,660 --> 00:14:23,060
 moving away from living in the grace of Christ.

296
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:24,100
 That's what he says.

297
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:28,140
 So the story of Galatians

298
00:14:28,140 --> 00:14:30,860
 actually points to all of our tendencies.

299
00:14:30,860 --> 00:14:34,460
 That we are, what's that song, "Prone to Wander," right?

300
00:14:34,460 --> 00:14:36,060
 What's the actual, it's a hymn.

301
00:14:36,060 --> 00:14:39,080
 I don't know hymns that well.

302
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:41,540
 But there's a line that says, "Prone to Wander."

303
00:14:41,540 --> 00:14:42,500
 Well, that's us.

304
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,620
 We're prone to wander.

305
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:46,260
 But people, we get off track all the time.

306
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:52,080
 But God had done this incredible saving work

307
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:53,040
 in the Galatians' life.

308
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:58,040
 And Paul, he takes them actually back to their experience.

309
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:03,280
 Because when Paul preached the gospel message,

310
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:07,940
 God called the Galatians to themselves.

311
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:09,800
 You know, whenever the gospel message is preached,

312
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:11,320
 God calls people to himself

313
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:13,280
 through the preaching of the gospel.

314
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:17,160
 And they responded with faith.

315
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:19,600
 And they received the Holy Spirit,

316
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:23,240
 experienced God's power working in their lives.

317
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:25,040
 And so Paul is taking them back to it.

318
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:27,320
 And then he's, but then he's like,

319
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:31,480
 but why are you now so quickly deserting

320
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:32,660
 the one who called you?

321
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:35,500
 Why are you turning away from him?

322
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:43,300
 And they're turning their backs on God's grace.

323
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:48,520
 So what was happening?

324
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:51,280
 And then he says that they're returning to a non-gospel,

325
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:54,180
 that the gospel message was perverted,

326
00:15:54,180 --> 00:15:56,500
 or they perverted the gospel of Christ.

327
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:58,300
 So what was this message?

328
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:01,580
 Well, the rival missionaries,

329
00:16:01,580 --> 00:16:03,980
 they added something to the gospel message.

330
00:16:03,980 --> 00:16:06,420
 So instead of it just being Christ's saving work,

331
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:09,660
 it's like they added a plus.

332
00:16:09,660 --> 00:16:12,020
 And then it was also circumcision

333
00:16:12,020 --> 00:16:14,820
 and observance of the law that was needed.

334
00:16:14,820 --> 00:16:20,960
 And Paul is saying that by doing that,

335
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:24,340
 they are completely changing the gospel.

336
00:16:24,340 --> 00:16:27,580
 It's not a gospel at all anymore when we do that.

337
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:31,220
 Because now what happens when you add something to,

338
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:33,060
 when there's something else that is needed

339
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:34,660
 to bring you into God's family,

340
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:37,700
 to make you a Christian besides Jesus'

341
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,660
 saving work on the cross,

342
00:16:39,660 --> 00:16:45,820
 what happens is you start putting Jesus aside

343
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:48,460
 because you don't really need Jesus.

344
00:16:48,460 --> 00:16:51,740
 And you start putting our own efforts in the center

345
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:54,480
 of law observing, of doing this, of doing that.

346
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:57,460
 And so Paul is saying like,

347
00:16:57,460 --> 00:17:00,340
 and that changes everything.

348
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:02,380
 That is no longer good news

349
00:17:02,380 --> 00:17:05,020
 because then you becoming part of God's family,

350
00:17:05,020 --> 00:17:07,180
 you living the empowered life has to do with you,

351
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:08,580
 not with Jesus.

352
00:17:08,580 --> 00:17:13,460
 And so let me try to,

353
00:17:13,460 --> 00:17:15,380
 we're gonna unpack this more throughout the series.

354
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:18,100
 This is today just scratching the surface with this.

