00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:21,180
 But let me unpack this a little bit more.

356
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:26,180
 So I have a definition of what the gospel is.

357
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:32,460
 So the heart of the gospel message

358
00:17:32,460 --> 00:17:36,140
 is that Christ died for our sins,

359
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:38,260
 that he freed us from the power of sin

360
00:17:38,260 --> 00:17:40,580
 and evil over our lives,

361
00:17:40,580 --> 00:17:42,500
 filled us with his Holy Spirit

362
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:46,540
 and brought us into a personal relationship with God.

363
00:17:46,540 --> 00:17:51,220
 Our right standing with God is 100% the work of Christ.

364
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:54,880
 100%, not like 80/20.

365
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:58,780
 We come empty handed to God.

366
00:17:58,780 --> 00:18:02,620
 There is nothing that we can do out of our own effort

367
00:18:02,620 --> 00:18:05,000
 to earn the right standing with God.

368
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,560
 We simply respond with repentance and faith

369
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:11,600
 to the good news and receive the gift of salvation.

370
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:19,260
 And whenever we add things to the gospel,

371
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:26,860
 then suddenly we start relying on our own efforts

372
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:29,340
 and we still do that today.

373
00:18:29,340 --> 00:18:31,900
 We still add things to the gospel message.

374
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:35,500
 Maybe it's like if you wanna be really a Christian,

375
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,320
 you not only need to believe in Jesus

376
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:38,540
 and receive his forgiveness

377
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:40,720
 and come to him with repentance, faith,

378
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:43,340
 but you also need to believe these certain doctrines

379
00:18:43,340 --> 00:18:45,700
 that a particular church holds

380
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:47,980
 and you need to do these certain actions.

381
00:18:47,980 --> 00:18:54,140
 And so then we're putting extra requirements

382
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:57,300
 in the way of people who God wants to come to,

383
00:18:57,300 --> 00:19:00,060
 that God wants for them to come to himself.

384
00:19:00,060 --> 00:19:01,980
 And then really what this, if you think about it too,

385
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:06,980
 is if it depends on us, what if we really have messed up?

386
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:13,260
 What if our life is such a mess?

387
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:17,660
 I mean, it would be hopeless for people like us

388
00:19:17,660 --> 00:19:20,360
 when our life is such a mess.

389
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:23,340
 How could we come to Jesus if it depends on us?

390
00:19:23,340 --> 00:19:27,100
 But because it's 100% the work of Jesus,

391
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:31,100
 the saving work, that's why anyone can come

392
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:35,140
 and God can restore and transform your life

393
00:19:35,140 --> 00:19:37,700
 and make you part of his family.

394
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:42,700
 And so Paul is saying the problem is,

395
00:19:42,700 --> 00:19:45,180
 and it's not a gospel at all,

396
00:19:45,180 --> 00:19:48,220
 is because they have added to the saving work of Christ,

397
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:51,120
 they have added these additional requirements.

398
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:53,780
 And that is a non-gospel,

399
00:19:53,780 --> 00:19:57,100
 it's a perversion of the gospel of Jesus Christ.

400
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:59,140
 So that's what Paul's saying, that's the issue,

401
00:19:59,140 --> 00:20:01,100
 because it's not just a little,

402
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,580
 oh, he did just have a little bit of a different pain,

403
00:20:02,580 --> 00:20:04,480
 no, it's a completely different thing.

404
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:11,420
 So this is the analysis of Paul from the situation.

405
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:12,820
 So that's the first thing that he does,

406
00:20:12,820 --> 00:20:16,180
 he takes the Galatian to the analysis of the situation.

407
00:20:16,180 --> 00:20:19,060
 Like this is completely different, this is no gospel,

408
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:21,500
 you are being misled by this.

409
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:23,540
 But then the second thing that Paul does,

410
00:20:23,540 --> 00:20:26,420
 he actually takes them also back

411
00:20:26,420 --> 00:20:28,540
 to the grace and peace of Jesus.

412
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:33,000
 He takes them back to the gospel message themselves

413
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,940
 because they're wondering, they've lost track,

414
00:20:34,940 --> 00:20:36,380
 they've lost their way.

415
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:38,260
 And what do we do when we lose our way?

416
00:20:38,260 --> 00:20:40,100
 Well, we come back to the cross of Jesus,

417
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:42,500
 we come back to the grace of Jesus.

418
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:46,740
 And we allow Jesus to minister to us,

419
00:20:46,740 --> 00:20:49,700
 we come again empty-handed and say,

420
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:52,100
 Jesus, I'm sorry, forgive me.

421
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:53,820
 And we receive this grace again,

422
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:56,260
 and we are strengthened and we are renewed

423
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:59,660
 in our discipleship, in our relationship.

424
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:02,700
 And so Paul, and this starts in verse three,

