00:21:28,040 --> 00:21:31,040
 Galatians is the only letter where Paul expands

434
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:36,040
 on that greeting, where he further unfolds

435
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:40,120
 what the gospel message entails.

436
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:41,360
 And it might have been even like

437
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:43,380
 a early Christian confession.

438
00:21:43,380 --> 00:21:44,960
 And so he takes them back to this message

439
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:48,080
 that he has proclaimed and wants to lead them back

440
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,960
 to this place of where they come empty handed,

441
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:52,280
 where it doesn't depend on their works,

442
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:56,960
 and where they just say, Jesus, I need you,

443
00:21:56,960 --> 00:22:00,400
 I surrender to you, I need you to forgive me,

444
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:04,000
 I need you to get me back on track because I'm off track.

445
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,360
 And that's how the Galatians started, right?

446
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:07,480
 So he's taking them also back

447
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:10,400
 to how they first became Christians.

448
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:11,600
 And I don't know if you ever do that.

449
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,960
 If you ever, in your own story,

450
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:16,540
 go back to what Jesus has done, I think we forget, right?

451
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:19,960
 We forget this amazing work that Jesus has done,

452
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,240
 we get distracted.

453
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,640
 And so Paul is taking them back to this amazing moment

454
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:25,840
 when they first became a Christian.

455
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:26,840
 And actually as Christians,

456
00:22:26,840 --> 00:22:29,080
 we need to continue to return to that.

457
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:32,920
 And we need to continue to receive the gospel message.

458
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:36,040
 The gospel message doesn't only bring us

