00:25:49,540 --> 00:25:51,860
 Well, that's what was happening, right?

528
00:25:51,860 --> 00:25:53,260
 There was a gospel being preached.

529
00:25:53,260 --> 00:25:56,100
 But it's interesting, he doesn't name the agitators.

530
00:25:56,100 --> 00:26:00,180
 He doesn't say, you know, Billy Bob is under curse

531
00:26:00,180 --> 00:26:01,340
 because he preached a different gospel.

532
00:26:01,340 --> 00:26:04,660
 He just gives this general statement.

533
00:26:04,660 --> 00:26:06,980
 Anyone, including himself.

534
00:26:07,940 --> 00:26:12,940
 So Paul is not looking for allegiance to himself.

535
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:18,900
 What he wants is bring the Galatians back to allegiance

536
00:26:18,900 --> 00:26:20,980
 to the true gospel message,

537
00:26:20,980 --> 00:26:24,940
 that they are committed to it, that they protect it,

538
00:26:24,940 --> 00:26:27,560
 that they understand it, that they guard it.

539
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:29,620
 I think that's a word for us as a church,

540
00:26:29,620 --> 00:26:36,580
 that we have an allegiance to the gospel message.

541
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:39,460
 That we protect it, that we guard it,

542
00:26:39,460 --> 00:26:41,460
 that we're careful with it ourselves.

543
00:26:41,460 --> 00:26:46,300
 So Paul, again, he's just bringing them back.

544
00:26:46,300 --> 00:26:48,140
 It's all about the gospel, bringing them back,

545
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:50,180
 you know, from all these different angles.

546
00:26:50,180 --> 00:26:56,460
 And then it's interesting, in verse 10, he says this.

547
00:26:56,460 --> 00:26:58,340
 "Am I now trying to win the approval

548
00:26:58,340 --> 00:27:00,980
 of human beings or of God?

549
00:27:00,980 --> 00:27:03,140
 Or am I trying to please people?

550
00:27:03,140 --> 00:27:05,340
 If I were still trying to please people,

551
00:27:05,340 --> 00:27:07,560
 I would not be a servant of Christ."

552
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:11,740
 Now, apparently the rival missionaries,

553
00:27:11,740 --> 00:27:14,940
 they had accused Paul of being a people pleaser.

554
00:27:14,940 --> 00:27:18,380
 That he proclaimed the gospel that people wanted to hear,

555
00:27:18,380 --> 00:27:21,500
 that was just meeting the itching of their ear.

556
00:27:21,500 --> 00:27:23,340
 That he left out the complicated parts,

557
00:27:23,340 --> 00:27:24,500
 that he only gave them half,

558
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:27,740
 and he left away the observing the law and circumcision.

559
00:27:27,740 --> 00:27:29,240
 He left away the hard parts.

560
00:27:30,780 --> 00:27:35,780
 And Paul is, I mean, he's already said verses one through nine,

561
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:38,260
 you know, it's already written all that.

562
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:41,620
 And he's like, "Hey, do I sound like a guy

563
00:27:41,620 --> 00:27:44,060
 who's trying to please people here?

564
00:27:44,060 --> 00:27:46,580
 Who announces curses and things?

565
00:27:46,580 --> 00:27:49,700
 Do I sound like a people pleaser to you?"

566
00:27:49,700 --> 00:27:52,660
 I mean, that's basically, so it's almost like ironic.

567
00:27:52,660 --> 00:27:55,220
 You know, he's asking the Galatians

568
00:27:55,220 --> 00:27:58,660
 who had apparently started believing in that accusation.

569
00:28:00,340 --> 00:28:04,620
 And what's interesting is that it says

570
00:28:04,620 --> 00:28:08,380
 that if I were still trying to please people,

571
00:28:08,380 --> 00:28:11,860
 so that means Paul used to please people.

572
00:28:11,860 --> 00:28:14,340
 He used to be a people pleaser.

573
00:28:14,340 --> 00:28:18,380
 And I think, I don't know about you,

574
00:28:18,380 --> 00:28:21,840
 people pleasing, I struggle with that.

575
00:28:21,840 --> 00:28:26,060
 You know, I like people,

576
00:28:26,060 --> 00:28:27,660
 I don't wanna rub anyone the wrong way.

577
00:28:27,660 --> 00:28:28,580
 I like people liking me.

578
00:28:28,580 --> 00:28:31,100
 I like harmony, I don't like conflict.

579
00:28:31,100 --> 00:28:34,020
 So sometimes it's just easier to people please, right?

580
00:28:34,020 --> 00:28:36,780
 So I think there's actually another thing

581
00:28:36,780 --> 00:28:39,620
 that gets us off track when we please people

582
00:28:39,620 --> 00:28:40,820
 instead of pleasing God.

583
00:28:40,820 --> 00:28:44,260
 It's also a way that we wander away from God.

584
00:28:44,260 --> 00:28:47,580
 And Paul is saying that he used to do that,

585
00:28:47,580 --> 00:28:50,900
 but something has changed, something has transformed him.

586
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:54,180
 And we even know what transformed

587
00:28:54,180 --> 00:28:58,420
 because he talks about moving from being a people pleaser

588
00:28:58,420 --> 00:29:02,380
 to now being a servant of Christ and pleasing God.

589
00:29:02,380 --> 00:29:04,900
 So there was somewhere along the way,

590
00:29:04,900 --> 00:29:06,740
 whether that, and I think this was already

591
00:29:06,740 --> 00:29:08,200
 during his Christian journey,

592
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:09,500
 not that he became a Christian,

593
00:29:09,500 --> 00:29:11,780
 then suddenly he stopped pleasing people completely.

594
00:29:11,780 --> 00:29:14,060
 I think there was still some time

595
00:29:14,060 --> 00:29:16,360
 where that needed to be worked out in his life.

596
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:20,860
 But where he was committed to doing God's will

597
00:29:20,860 --> 00:29:24,820
 above all else, where he was committed to serving Jesus

598
00:29:24,820 --> 00:29:27,820
 and not to make, you know, please people

599
00:29:27,820 --> 00:29:29,420
 and do what they wanted to hear.

600
00:29:29,420 --> 00:29:33,260
 Now, what are some ways that we please people today?

601
00:29:33,260 --> 00:29:37,460
 Well, we do that in businesses, in our workplaces.

602
00:29:37,460 --> 00:29:38,940
 We do that in our relationships.

603
00:29:38,940 --> 00:29:41,420
 We do that, it happens in the education field,

604
00:29:41,420 --> 00:29:43,660
 families, social media.

605
00:29:43,660 --> 00:29:45,940
 Just think of social media.

606
00:29:45,940 --> 00:29:51,580
 When you create a post, carefully crafted,

607
00:29:51,580 --> 00:29:54,780
 hours spent, the right filter.

608
00:29:54,780 --> 00:29:57,120
 Actually, I'm not even good at social media myself.

609
00:29:57,120 --> 00:29:58,940
 So I'm probably the wrong person to talk about this.

610
00:29:58,940 --> 00:30:01,460
 You know, doing this incredible IG story.

611
00:30:01,460 --> 00:30:03,580
 I mean, what are we looking for?

612
00:30:03,580 --> 00:30:05,680
 We're looking for people's approval of us

613
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:08,380
 that affirm our worth, that say, wow, you're amazing.

614
00:30:08,380 --> 00:30:10,780
 Isn't that true?

615
00:30:10,780 --> 00:30:12,360
 I think so.

616
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:16,580
 And we also want to avoid getting backlash.

617
00:30:16,580 --> 00:30:17,940
 Has anyone ever gotten backlash

618
00:30:17,940 --> 00:30:20,100
 on some of their social media posts?

619
00:30:20,100 --> 00:30:21,300
 I have.

620
00:30:21,300 --> 00:30:23,180
 I once had 100 messages.

621
00:30:23,180 --> 00:30:26,020
 I touched a subject in the US

622
00:30:26,020 --> 00:30:28,140
 that was about gun violence

623
00:30:28,140 --> 00:30:32,320
 after the Las Vegas shooting,

624
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:33,620
 and it got really personal.

625
00:30:33,620 --> 00:30:36,420
 We were talking about why do we have

626
00:30:36,420 --> 00:30:38,820
 so many automatic weapons and blah, blah, blah.

627
00:30:38,820 --> 00:30:41,740
 So honestly, after that experience,

628
00:30:41,740 --> 00:30:43,940
 I also am a little bit careful what I say.

629
00:30:43,940 --> 00:30:45,900
 I don't want to deal with the backlash.

630
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:52,820
 But when I was a pastor in the US,

631
00:30:52,820 --> 00:30:57,500
 I wanted to immerse myself in the community,

632
00:30:57,500 --> 00:30:58,460
 not just the Christian community,

633
00:30:58,460 --> 00:30:59,940
 but actually just the community where I was living.

634
00:30:59,940 --> 00:31:02,260
 And so I decided to volunteer in a library,

635
00:31:02,260 --> 00:31:03,860
 in a public library.

636
00:31:03,860 --> 00:31:07,500
 So I helped out with cleaning the office, the background.

637
00:31:07,500 --> 00:31:09,700
 I started shelving books, whatever they needed.

638
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:11,780
 I just helped out and was getting to know people

639
00:31:11,780 --> 00:31:13,540
 while I was doing that.

640
00:31:13,540 --> 00:31:16,160
 So after being there for a while,

641
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:17,700
 one of the employees asked me

642
00:31:17,700 --> 00:31:21,980
 to start scanning out 20 books

643
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:23,100
 or checking out 20 books

644
00:31:23,100 --> 00:31:24,780
 and then just put them in the return box.

645
00:31:24,780 --> 00:31:26,180
 And I do that multiple times.

646
00:31:26,180 --> 00:31:28,780
 So I started doing that.

647
00:31:28,780 --> 00:31:30,500
 And after a while, I was thinking,

648
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:32,020
 I was like, what am I doing here?

649
00:31:32,020 --> 00:31:34,820
 Why am I checking out books in the library,

650
00:31:34,820 --> 00:31:35,900
 taking them from their shelf,

651
00:31:35,900 --> 00:31:37,700
 put them in the return box?

652
00:31:37,700 --> 00:31:40,260
 And so I realized that I was somehow

653
00:31:40,260 --> 00:31:44,700
 manipulating some book circulation statistics or something

654
00:31:44,700 --> 00:31:47,080
 that probably was needed for whether it's local

655
00:31:47,080 --> 00:31:49,620
 or government funding or something.

656
00:31:49,620 --> 00:31:50,980
 But you know what?

657
00:31:50,980 --> 00:31:51,860
 I was a people pleaser.

658
00:31:51,860 --> 00:31:52,700
 I kept doing it.

659
00:31:52,700 --> 00:31:58,420
 Now it bothered me so much the next week

660
00:31:58,420 --> 00:32:00,780
 that when I came back, I was like,

661
00:32:00,780 --> 00:32:01,940
 if he asked me to do it,

662
00:32:01,940 --> 00:32:04,620
 I'm gonna say that I don't wanna do it.

663
00:32:04,620 --> 00:32:06,500
 And so that's what I'm doing.

664
00:32:06,500 --> 00:32:09,300
 And truth of the matter, I'm volunteering, right?

665
00:32:09,300 --> 00:32:11,220
 What do I have to lose?

666
00:32:11,220 --> 00:32:13,140
 So even so stupid to even try to please someone

667
00:32:13,140 --> 00:32:14,440
 where you're volunteering.

668
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:16,600
 (audience laughing)

669
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:18,740
 But then think about when it's in places

670
00:32:18,740 --> 00:32:20,420
 where it really matters.

671
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:21,860
 You know, when it's about a family,

672
00:32:21,860 --> 00:32:24,200
 where not you're gonna have a paycheck

673
00:32:24,200 --> 00:32:26,460
 and you ask to compromise and manipulate something

674
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:28,480
 or evade taxes or whatever it may be.

675
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:31,780
 Then it's different.

676
00:32:31,780 --> 00:32:34,060
 So that's one way that we also get off track.

677
00:32:34,060 --> 00:32:39,060
 And Paul, he's giving us an example of,

678
00:32:39,060 --> 00:32:41,940
 you know, when we have security

679
00:32:41,940 --> 00:32:43,820
 of Jesus's work in our lives,

680
00:32:43,820 --> 00:32:49,140
 when we can just rest in that we are loved,

681
00:32:49,140 --> 00:32:52,180
 we are accepted, you know, by God,

682
00:32:52,180 --> 00:32:57,340
 then that actually frees us up

683
00:32:57,340 --> 00:33:00,560
 to the need to be people pleasers.

684
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:02,760
 You know, it can be really transformative

685
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:05,780
 as our identity in Christ gets more and more solid.

686
00:33:05,780 --> 00:33:09,420
 We have less and less the need to need to please people.

687
00:33:09,420 --> 00:33:13,060
 And so Paul was encouraging the Galatians

688
00:33:13,060 --> 00:33:16,220
 also in the strong identity formation,

689
00:33:16,220 --> 00:33:18,220
 you know, that they more and more become people

690
00:33:18,220 --> 00:33:23,220
 who choose to please God and instead of pleasing man.

691
00:33:23,220 --> 00:33:28,380
 Now, where does all of this leave us?

692
00:33:28,380 --> 00:33:31,620
 And I wanna invite the worship team to come up at this point.

693
00:33:31,620 --> 00:33:34,540
 All right, at the beginning of the sermon, I asked,

694
00:33:34,540 --> 00:33:38,660
 so what do you do when you lose your way as a Christian?

695
00:33:38,660 --> 00:33:41,440
 How do you find your way back into the life

696
00:33:41,440 --> 00:33:43,240
 that God is calling you to live?

697
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:45,900
 And we saw several things.

698
00:33:45,900 --> 00:33:48,900
 For one, maybe we understand what has misled us

699
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:51,940
 or taken us away from the life of God in the first place.

700
00:33:51,940 --> 00:33:55,200
 And then maybe today as I was sharing,

701
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:57,700
 there was actually some things that came up for yourself,

702
00:33:57,700 --> 00:34:01,620
 like, where you're like, wow, it can be business,

703
00:34:01,620 --> 00:34:04,940
 it can be other priorities, it can be many different things.

704
00:34:04,940 --> 00:34:07,840
 Can be people pleasing.

705
00:34:07,840 --> 00:34:12,420
 But then we also looked, what does Paul do?

706
00:34:12,420 --> 00:34:14,260
 Well, he takes them back to the gospel.

707
00:34:14,260 --> 00:34:19,220
 He takes them back to this when they encountered Jesus

708
00:34:19,220 --> 00:34:23,500
 for the first time and experienced just as love and grace

709
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:26,940
 where they came empty handed to him, they had nothing.

710
00:34:26,940 --> 00:34:31,060
 And he received them, he brought them into his family.

711
00:34:31,060 --> 00:34:34,600
 That was not because they met some circumcision

712
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:37,620
 or other requirements or believed these 20 doctrines

713
00:34:37,620 --> 00:34:40,140
 and did 20 acts of service a day.

714
00:34:41,220 --> 00:34:45,540
 It was just because Jesus loves them,

715
00:34:45,540 --> 00:34:47,840
 forgives them and gives them grace.

716
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:55,540
 And so, and then we saw that Paul also just shows

717
00:34:55,540 --> 00:35:00,100
 that he really wants us, the gospel to be centered

718
00:35:00,100 --> 00:35:02,660
 in our life, that we meditate on it,

719
00:35:02,660 --> 00:35:05,420
 that we don't lose track of it

720
00:35:05,420 --> 00:35:08,500
 because it also helps us as a church, as individuals,

721
00:35:08,500 --> 00:35:10,400
 to stay on track of what Jesus has for us,

722
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:12,640
 that we live by his grace and mercy.

723
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:18,900
 And when you live by grace instead of your own achievements,

724
00:35:18,900 --> 00:35:23,020
 you're less judgmental, you're less prideful

725
00:35:23,020 --> 00:35:24,920
 because you know you don't deserve it.

726
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:28,700
 And you just really live a different life.

727
00:35:28,700 --> 00:35:33,380
 And so that's where Jesus is inviting us.

728
00:35:33,380 --> 00:35:35,480
 He goes, I wanna invite everyone to stand.

729
00:35:39,460 --> 00:35:42,720
 And if you've been wondering, you know what,

730
00:35:42,720 --> 00:35:44,560
 whatever it may be, if you feel like, man,

731
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:45,760
 I've gotten off track in my faith,

732
00:35:45,760 --> 00:35:47,480
 maybe I'm not as passionate as I wanna be,

733
00:35:47,480 --> 00:35:51,600
 maybe I'm totally doing illegal, wrong things,

734
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:55,920
 pleasing people, but you know, whatever it may be,

735
00:35:55,920 --> 00:36:00,920
 I wanna invite you to actually just come right now.

736
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:03,360
 Jesus is here, just to come to him,

737
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,800
 to turn to him, to his presence

738
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:10,800
 and just to receive his grace and forgiveness again.

739
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:12,840
 And I wanna encourage you to just,

740
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:14,660
 if that's you, just stretch out your hands before,

741
00:36:14,660 --> 00:36:16,860
 you know, just love to pray over you right now.

742
00:36:16,860 --> 00:36:20,360
 If you're saying, Jesus, I need you,

743
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:25,820
 I'm sorry, I've wondered, will you show me your grace again?

744
00:36:25,820 --> 00:36:28,420
 Just stretch out your hand and let me pray over you.

745
00:36:28,420 --> 00:36:33,160
 So Jesus, I thank you that you are the God

746
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:35,480
 who brings people back on track.

747
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:38,860
 You meet us in our wondering,

748
00:36:38,860 --> 00:36:41,280
 we're unfaithful, but you are faithful.

749
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:46,120
 You love us and you love showing us your grace.

750
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:48,920
 You love showing us your goodness.

751
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:50,040
 And I pray for everyone right now

752
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:52,440
 that feels like they've been off track,

753
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:56,120
 that you renew them right now through your forgiveness,

754
00:36:56,120 --> 00:36:58,320
 that you renew them through your grace,

755
00:36:58,320 --> 00:37:00,520
 through your love, through acceptance,

756
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:01,960
 and that you strengthen them.

757
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:07,240
 That you strengthen the resolve to be servants of you,

758
00:37:07,240 --> 00:37:08,760
 to please you.

759
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:13,520
 I pray that you root them deeper and deeper

760
00:37:13,520 --> 00:37:15,000
 in your love for them,

761
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:20,760
 and the identity that you give us as your beloved children.

762
00:37:20,760 --> 00:37:24,560
 I pray, Holy Spirit, that you make that real,

763
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:28,720
 that this is something we can feel and we know.

764
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:31,300
 (gentle music)

765
00:37:31,300 --> 00:37:34,120
 Thank you, Holy Spirit.

766
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:36,820
 Thank you for your work right now.

767
00:37:36,820 --> 00:37:40,640
 Thank you, Jesus, for your grace.

768
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:43,040
 Thank you for your mercy.

769
00:37:43,040 --> 00:37:48,800
 Thank you that in you, we can always start anew.

770
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,440
 Doesn't matter what has happened.

771
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:55,440
 So I pray for your blessing over us as a church,

772
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:57,320
 that you strengthen us with your grace,

773
00:37:57,320 --> 00:37:58,480
 that you pour your love over us,

774
00:37:58,480 --> 00:38:04,600
 I pray this in your name Jesus. Amen. Let's let's worship.

